Global Pressure Groundwood Pulp (PGW) Market Insights
Pressure Groundwood Pulp (PGW) Market size was valued at USD 7.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 10.2 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 4.1% from 2024 to 2030.

Pressure Groundwood Pulp (PGW) Market Overview
The global Pressure Groundwood Pulp (PGW) market is a significant segment of the pulp and paper industry, primarily utilized in the production of newsprint and certain types of paper products. As of 2021, the market was valued at approximately USD 162.3 billion, with projections indicating a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 2.7% from 2022 to 2027, potentially reaching nearly USD 190 billion by 2027. This growth is driven by the increasing demand for paper products, particularly in emerging markets, and the rising preference for sustainable and recyclable materials. The Asia Pacific region holds the largest share of the PGW market, driven by strong demand in countries like China and India. North America and Europe also contribute significantly, with a focus on sustainability and recycling. However, the market faces challenges such as competition from alternative materials, fluctuating raw material prices, and environmental regulations. Despite these challenges, the PGW market presents opportunities for growth, especially in sustainable packaging and tissue paper segments. Source

